= Houdini Ocean Procedural Configure =
#context: lop
#type: node

"""Configures a USD primitive to render as a Houdini Ocean surface using the ocean rendering procedural."""

== Overview ==

Houdini Ocean Procedural Configure assigns the Houdini Ocean rendering procedural to a USD mesh primitive, so the displaced ocean surface (and optional foam and interior volume) is generated at render time from cached ocean spectrum data rather than being baked into the stage.

Feed the node the ocean spectrum and mask caches written by the ocean SOP tools, point it at the surface mesh primitive on the input stage, and assign the materials used for the surface, interior and proxy.

WARNING:
    The Karma/Mantra render command must include `--allowed-procedurals all` for the ocean procedural to load.

@parameters

== Spectrum ==

Spectrum File:
    #id: spectrumfile
    Ocean spectrum geometry cache used to displace and animate the surface.

Mask File:
    #id: maskfile
    Optional mask geometry cache that limits the ocean deformation.

Time:
    #id: time
    Time at which the ocean spectrum is evaluated. Default: `$T`.

== Geometry ==

Surface Mesh Primitive:
    #id: rendergeo
    USD primitive of the ocean surface mesh to render with the procedural.

Enable Interior:
    #id: enableinterior
    Renders an interior (underwater) volume below the surface.

Interior Mesh Primitive:
    #id: interiorgeo
    USD primitive used as the interior volume boundary.

Viewport Quality:
    #id: viewportquality
    Tessellation quality of the surface preview shown in the viewport.

== Dicing ==

Dicing Quality:
    #id: dicingquality
    Render-time tessellation quality of the ocean surface.

Screen Window Size:
    #id: winsize
    Screen-space window size used when dicing the surface.

Downsample:
    #id: downsample
    Reduces the resolution of the evaluated spectrum to speed up dicing.

Anti-Alias Blur:
    #id: aablur
    Amount of blur applied to reduce aliasing on the diced surface.

Verbose:
    #id: verbose
    Prints procedural diagnostics during rendering.

== Shading ==

Materials Path:
    #id: materials_path
    Scope on the stage that holds the ocean materials. Default: `/$OS`.

Surface Material:
    #id: surfacematerial
    Material bound to the ocean surface. The adjacent toggle enables the assignment.

Interior Material:
    #id: interiormaterial
    Material bound to the interior volume. The adjacent toggle enables the assignment.

Proxy Material:
    #id: proxymaterial
    Material bound to the proxy representation. The adjacent toggle enables the assignment.

Point Velocity:
    #id: pointvel
    Outputs point velocities so the surface can be motion blurred.

Cusp:
    #id: cusp
    Sharpens wave crests, controlled by the cusp range, gamma and intensity.

Enable Foam:
    #id: enablefoam
    Renders foam from a foam particle cache, with Foam Pattern controls for streaks, bubbles and displacement.

Foam Particles:
    #id: foamfile
    Foam particle geometry cache used when foam is enabled.
